{"id":"furlong","term":"Furlong","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A stadium, a Greek measure of distance equal to 606 feet and 9 inches (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 24:13\">Luke 24:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 6:19\">John 6:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 11:18\">11:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 14:20\">Rev. 14:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 21:16\">21:16</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Luke 24:13","John 6:19","John 11:18","Revelation 14:20","Revelation 21:16"]}